<span id="freeTextContainer16012924711355899835">Will Self has been likened to Martin Amis, and although this is the only book I&apos;ve read by Self, I can see the comparison. <br/><br/>The characters are people you might avoid in real life (or be manipulated by them). <br/><br/>What makes this book so readable is the introspection of the narrator/main character. He&apos;s a fascinating misanthrope in a surreal quandary. </span>
  <span id="freeText16012924711355899835" style="display:none">Will Self has been likened to Martin Amis, and although this is the only book I've read by Self, I can see the comparison. <br /><br />The characters are people you might avoid in real life (or be manipulated by them). <br /><br />What makes this book so readable is the introspection of the narrator/main character. He's a fascinating misanthrope in a surreal quandary. </span>
