        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1335784561" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14566041491989595314">Even in a work as early as this, Self is clearly a very talented writer. The sentences alone are enough to get this book a two star review. I also liked the way the book explored the limitations of different psychological/psychiatric models as explanations for the main character&apos;s experiences. I didn&apos;t really feel that the over the top violence (really only in a few sections) was justified, though, and the ending was a little cheap with the sudden shift in point of view. Maybe it was coming to t</span>
  <span id="freeText14566041491989595314" style="display:none">Even in a work as early as this, Self is clearly a very talented writer. The sentences alone are enough to get this book a two star review. I also liked the way the book explored the limitations of different psychological/psychiatric models as explanations for the main character's experiences. I didn't really feel that the over the top violence (really only in a few sections) was justified, though, and the ending was a little cheap with the sudden shift in point of view. Maybe it was coming to this after reading Umbrella, which I absolutely loved, but this one was slightly disappointing.</span>
  <a data-text-id="14566041491989595314" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


